DESCRIPTION:This hands-on stitching workshop introduces participants to the basics of hand stitching\, crochet\, and simple craft-making techniques. Led by Zoya\, the session focuses on creativity\, patience\, and self-expression through textiles. Participants will explore how everyday materials can be transformed into meaningful handmade pieces. The workshop is designed to be inclusive and accessible\, encouraging participants of all skill levels to learn\, create\, and connect.
DTEND:20260621T083000Z
DTSTART:20260621T053000Z
SUMMARY:Stitching Stories
UID:1309@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/stitching-stories/
